1.title: Who Are the Anunnaki?
1.plot: Ancient gods and deities have been spoken about and worshiped by mankind for thousands of years. From cuneiform tablets and religious text discovered around the world, mighty gods known by the Sumerians as the Anunnaki were detailed and depicted. Are these merely stories and myths, or part of actual history necessary to understand the true story of humanity? - Travel with us across the globe as we uncover evidence to find out who the Anunnaki really are and to separate simple myth from fact. From the story of Noah in the Atrahasis to the creation epic of Earth known ...

2.title: Mayan Realm of the Wizard Kings
2.plot: Hidden deep in the jungles of the Mesoamerica, the lost civilizations of the Maya and Olmec are just now being fully uncovered and understood. Could these advanced cultures have been influenced by similar gods portrayed thousands of miles away in Egypt and Mesopotamia? - Relics and artifacts found from Chichen Itza to Palenque shown striking similarities to that of ancient astronauts and advanced technology for viewing the stars. Are we missing what our ancestors were trying to tell us all along about the Anunnaki?

3.title: Birth of Noah and Tenochtitlan
3.plot: From the Book of Enoch, Noah's amazing alien birth prompts father Lamech to seek counsel from his father Methuselah, and then his father Enoch whom we are told resides with the Gods. Could the banishment of Qayin by Enlil-Yahweh lead to the land of Nod, east of Eden? Where was the city of Enoch, that Qayin (Biblical Cain) built for his son while "wandering" in exile? Join us as we survey the evidence from Sumer to the Mesoamerican lost realm of the winged serpent, where the ancient Aztec race abandons the great temple site of Teotihuacan for a new home. 4.title: Calendar Quarrel, Mayan Long Count
4.plot: Ancient temples around the world were ingeniously constructed to align to solstice and equinox events. We now know that Magi, Kings, and their astrologers watched the heavens in order to establish accurate zodiacal time, a means by which even the Anunnaki gods used to set their ruler ship term limits. What could possibly go wrong among such highly educated observers and mathematicians of ages past that led to calendar squabbles and new civilizations, including the Mesoamerican Maya? The notion that the calendar was created by and for farmers advising them when to sow ...
